      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "The F1717 compression-bending simulation is quasi-static with a direct sparse solver (SPARSE) and no iterative convergence tolerance sensitivity. Numerical solver error is distinct from discretization error only when iterative solvers with non-trivial tolerance settings are employed. Because the analysis uses a direct solver, residual-based solver error is identically zero by construction and this factor is not applicable to the computational approach used here. Scoped out per ASME VV40 §6.3.2 guidance permitting exclusion of factors with no meaningful contribution to total numerical error."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-ue",
