      "rationale": "The quantities of interest (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly specified by ASTM F1717 and are the regulatory submission QoIs. Because the QoIs are normatively defined by the applicable standard and adopted verbatim as the model prediction targets, there is no analytical latitude in QoI selection to assess. Relevance of the QoIs to the COU is self-evident by regulatory definition, and a separate credibility factor assessment would be tautological. Scoped out per ASME VV40 §6.3.6 guidance permitting exclusion when QoIs are normatively mandated."
